    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lankas reviews Renewable Energy Plans",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Minister of Power and Energy Kanchana Wijsekara says that a productive discussion was held between the Ceylon Electricity Board and officials from the Sustainable Energy Authorities this morning (26) to review the progress on Renewable Energy Plans.",
        "\"Discussed proposed 100 MW Solar plant in Siyambalanduwa, EOIs, Floating Solar, Tariffs, Grid Capacity, Signing of PPA. Appointed a joint committee with CEB & SEA officials to finalize RE plans\", Minister Kanchana said.",
        "Linking lives and villages: Gammadda launches bridge construction in remote Kegalle",
        "Children need to be at heart of resolving SL crisis: UNICEF regional director"
      ],
